{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"46078e8b-7d41-4de4-8c18-44174c7dad2c","agentId":"a51538fe1f825e7ea","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Feature: Conway's Game of Life - Next Generation\n\nTest file: src/game-of-life.spec.ts\nImplementation file: src/game-of-life.ts\n\nRequirements:\n- Implement Conway's Game of Life with an infinite grid (sparse representation)\n- Export function: `export function nextGeneration(cells: Cell[]): Cell[]` where `type Cell = [number, number]`\n- Rules:\n  1. Underpopulation: Any live cell with fewer than 2 live neighbors dies\n  2. Survival: Any live cell with 2 or 3 live neighbors lives on\n  3. Overpopulation: Any live cell with more than 3 live neighbors dies\n  4. Reproduction: Any dead cell with exactly 3 live neighbors becomes alive\n\n- Examples from the spec:\n  - Single cell dies: [(0,0)] → []\n  - Two adjacent cells die (underpopulation): [(0,1), (1,1)] → []\n  - Block (still life): [(0,0), (1,0), (0,1), (1,1)] → unchanged\n  - Blinker (oscillator): [(0,0), (0,1), (0,2)] → [(-1,1), (0,1), (1,1)]\n  - Reproduction: dead cell with exactly 3 neighbors becomes alive\n  - Overpopulation: center cell with >3 neighbors dies\n\n- Handle negative coordinates\n- Input/output are arrays of [x, y] coordinate tuples\n\nEXPERIMENT MODE: Run autonomously, no HITL checkpoints."},"uuid":"c2569afe-de06-4007-b772-7bb469ac1387","timestamp":"2026-05-14T18:39:05.424Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"sdk-cli","cwd":"/home/experimenter/experiments/runs/2026-05-14_18-38-28_game-of-life-example-mapping_v4-exact-subagents_opus-4-6-portkey-no-thinking","sessionId":"61586c7a-6a5d-4e91-be53-014301eecbe1","version":"2.1.107","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"delightful-floating-snowglobe"}
